load("../allplots_smooth_models_agb.rda")

disturbed=merged[merged$Treatment=="disturbed",]
control=merged[merged$Treatment=="control",]

** model fits a separate smooth of Year for each subplot, but with a shared smoothing penalty (so all subplots borrow information from each other). ** AND tests whether the rate or shape of AGB change through time varies with temperature

Code 
#hierarchical smoothing - fs (smooths are fitted simultaneously using a single likelihood) VS independent smoothing.

mod_fs <- gam(
  agb ~ s(Year, subplot, bs = "fs", k = 8) + mean_z_tmax*Treatment, 
  data = merged,
  method = "REML"
)

Code 
# Subplot term: Each subplot has a unique, significant temporal AGB trajectory (differences in baseline biomass, recovery, or growth trends).
# 
# Temperature term: Adding temperature anomalies does not significantly alter these trajectories — meaning AGB changes through time are largely driven by subplot characteristics (stand structure, species, etc.), not by short-term temperature variation.

mod_fs1 <- gam(
  agb ~ s(Year, subplot, bs = "fs", k = 8) + s(mean_z_tmax, by=Treatment, k = 8), 
  data = merged,
  method = "REML"
)
